fields.name: Shakshuka
fields.description: \u003Cp\u003EShakshuka is a Middle Eastern dish of poached eggs in a flavorful tomato sauce with onions, peppers, garlic, and spices like cumin and paprika. It\u0027s often served with crusty bread for dipping and enjoyed for breakfast or brunch.\u003C/p\u003E
fields.instructions: \u003Col\u003E\u003Cli data\u002Dlist\u003D\u0022ordered\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class\u003D\u0022ql\u002Dui\u0022 contenteditable\u003D\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECook the veggies\u003C/strong\u003E: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and bell pepper, cooking until softened (about 5\u002D7 minutes). Add garlic and cook for another minute.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli data\u002Dlist\u003D\u0022ordered\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class\u003D\u0022ql\u002Dui\u0022 contenteditable\u003D\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMake the sauce\u003C/strong\u003E: Stir in the diced tomatoes, cumin, paprika, chili flakes, salt, and pepper. Simmer for 10\u002D15 minutes until the sauce thickens.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli data\u002Dlist\u003D\u0022ordered\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class\u003D\u0022ql\u002Dui\u0022 contenteditable\u003D\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPoach the eggs\u003C/strong\u003E: Make small wells in the sauce with a spoon. Crack the eggs into each well. Cover the skillet and cook for 5\u002D7 minutes, or until the eggs are cooked to your desired doneness.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli data\u002Dlist\u003D\u0022ordered\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class\u003D\u0022ql\u002Dui\u0022 contenteditable\u003D\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGarnish and serve\u003C/strong\u003E: Sprinkle with fresh herbs and serve with crusty bread for dipping.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E
